Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/inCapacity
Object: Relates a contribution to an incumbency of the person making the contribution e.g. a person making a contribution in their capacity of holding a CEO position of an organisation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/Incumbency
Object: A position held by a person for a period of time. e.g. Philip Hammond occupying the position of Foreign Secretary between two dates.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/displayOrder
Object: Relates a contribution type to its display order.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/
Object: A model describing contributions made by people or groups.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/Contribution
Object: A contribution by an individual or organisation to a document or committee inquiry etc.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/ContributionRole
Object: The type of contribution made. Might be as an author or reviewer or inquiry witness etc.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/isPublic
Object: Relates a contribution to whether not that contribution is made public. The is public flag will by necessity not be public.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/makesContribution
Object: Relates a person or group to a contribution they've made.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/hasContributionRole
Object: Relates a contribution to the type of contribution made.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contribution/Agent
Object: An agent. The superset of all people and all groups of people.
